reviews.review_text: great recording, very WET night at red rocks All 3 of these shows were great.  I think the 29th is the best of the 3 myself.  On this night Phil's side of the stage was literally underwater with Phil standing in a puddle for most of the evening.  Didn't slow him down a bit with some great big bass notes you could probably hear all the way in Denver!  Check the beginning of Playin (including the tuning part) and toward the end of the Other One where he just kinda starts playing big fat bass chords, just great.  Security at the Rocks was always oppressive, they even had a little holding cell that they would keep you in if you were vending or consuming in the parking lot, just until the show was over, then they would let you go.  I had to get into one of these shows "In Cognito" as I narrowly escaped capture by one of their THUGS for selling a few shirts on my way in.  They had a search party out for me and I hid in my buddy's van, changed my clothes,  wrapped my big head of hair in a scarf, put some sunglasses on and in I went.

Nice Show.  Nice Recording. Love your stories guys.  Had a good laugh.  This is a good show recorded very well by Jim Wise.  I consider this an FOB, hand-held (with the close-in whooping), and probably 2/3 back if not in the "sweet spot" with the clarity and the fidelity being top notch.  Don't recall a PITB Reprise being Reprised unless my memory says they did it in Cleveland on 3.2.81.  This is a solidly played average show (which of course is very good) but the stellar recording ups the stars to four.  My only beef is the outro crowd being cut too quickly, loosing that much loved ambience of being there.
Awesome Show Straight out from the east coat - loved this show.  Girl in front said "nothing but space" when it was over - she was right!
